        <h4 id="borsch">Borscht</h4>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 40 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 6 bowls</li>
        </ul>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/Borscht_served.jpg/1920px-Borscht_served.jpg" alt="Borscht" width = "400">
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th class="headings">Ingredients</th>
                    <th class="headings">Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Graund beef</td>
                    <td>500 gramm</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cabbage</td>
                    <td>200 gramm</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Potato</td>
                    <td>3 medium size</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Carrot</td>
                    <td>1 big</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Beet</td>
                    <td>1 big</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Onion</td>
                    <td>1 small</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1 tea spoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Put 1 gallon of water on the stove and put meatballs in the boiled water.
</p>
 <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Cut all vegies and put in the water in order: cabbage, potato, beet, carrot, onion. Add salt.</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Boiled for 20 min.</p>
